SHANGHAI COPPER ENDS MOSTLY UP IN SLOW TRADING . Shanghai copper futures ended mostly higher in slow trade on Thursday on speculative buying by retail investors . But many institutions were sidelined as copper on the London Metal Exchange ( LME ) hovered between $ 2 , 250 and $ 2 , 300 , traders said . The LME copper hovered between just under $ 2 , 300 and just above $ 2 , 260 , remaining well within its well - worn range on Wednesday . Business in the last three months was at $ 2 , 290 a tonne , up $ 12 from Tuesday . In Shanghai , the most actively traded December 1997 contract ended at 21 , 250 yuan ( $ 2 , 563 ) per tonne , rising 40 yuan . It opened at 21 , 250 yuan , hitting an intraday high of 21 , 300 and a low of 21 , 230 . August rose 40 yuan to 20 , 790 , September 10 to 20 , 900 , October 30 to 21 , 180 , November 20 to 21 , 250 and the January 1997 contract was unchanged at 21 , 250 . Combined volume fell to 12 , 090 tonnes from 25 , 870 . Copper opened slightly higher and moved in a very narrow range for most of the session . Traders said many investors remained on the sidelines due to a lack of market - moving news . " Speculative buying from retail investors was responsible for today ' s gains but the short - term market trend is still unclear , " one trader said . " Volume is thin , indicating most investors are waiting for clearer direction from the LME , " he added . In Shanghai , physical copper prices are around the 20 , 800 yuan level , little changed from Wednesday ' s close due to sluggishness on the futures market . Traders said copper was likely to continue moving in a narrow range in the short term if there was no market - moving news . Aluminium ended mixed . August rose 80 to 14 , 600 yuan per tonne , September was unchanged at 14 , 750 , October put on 180 to 15 , 000 , November was unchanged at 14 , 980 and December was flat at 15 , 050 . Combined volume rose to 3 , 090 tonnes from 2 , 810 . ( $ 1 . 0 = 8 . 2893 yuan ) - - Shanghai Newsroom ( 86 ) 21 - 6279 7004 ; Fax 21 - 6279 - 7174 
